You cannot delete items in DynamoDB without providing the primary key (partition + sort).  

You would have to do the following:

1. Create a GSI with the partition key `date` (call it `date-index`):
```
aws dynamodb update-table \
    --table-name test-items \
    --attribute-definitions AttributeName=date,AttributeType=S  \
    --global-secondary-index-updates \
        &quot;[
            {
                \&quot;Create\&quot;: {
                    \&quot;IndexName\&quot;: \&quot;date-index\&quot;,
                    \&quot;KeySchema\&quot;: [{\&quot;AttributeName\&quot;:\&quot;date\&quot;,\&quot;KeyType\&quot;:\&quot;HASH\&quot;}],
                    \&quot;Projection\&quot;:{
                        \&quot;ProjectionType\&quot;:\&quot;KEYS_ONLY\&quot;
                    }
                }
            }
        ]&quot;
``` 

2.  [Query][1] the table for the items you want to remove 
```
aws dynamodb query \
    --table-name test-items \
    --index-name date-index \
    --key-condition-expression &quot;#d = :badday&quot; \
    --expression-attribute-names &#39;{&quot;#d&quot;: &quot;date&quot;}&#39; \
    --expression-attribute-values  &#39;{&quot;:badday&quot;:{&quot;S&quot;:&quot;20220212&quot;}}&#39;
```
You will get a list of items:
```
{
    &quot;Items&quot;: [
        {
            &quot;date&quot;: {
                &quot;S&quot;: &quot;20220212&quot;
            },
            &quot;personKey&quot;: {
                &quot;S&quot;: &quot;456&quot;
            }
        },
        {
            &quot;date&quot;: {
                &quot;S&quot;: &quot;20220212&quot;
            },
            &quot;personKey&quot;: {
                &quot;S&quot;: &quot;123&quot;
            }
        }
    ],
    &quot;Count&quot;: 2,
    &quot;ScannedCount&quot;: 2,
    &quot;ConsumedCapacity&quot;: null
}
```
3. Record the primary keys of the offending records. 

4. Delete them one-by-one:
```
aws dynamodb delete-item \
    --table-name test-items \
    --key &#39;{&quot;personKey&quot;: {&quot;S&quot;: &quot;456&quot;}, &quot;date&quot;: {&quot;S&quot;: &quot;20220212&quot;}}&#39;
```

Note that a more cost-effective way to remove a large number of items from the table may be to copy the items you want to keep into a new table and then delete the old table.


  [1]: https://docs.aws.amazon.com/amazondynamodb/latest/developerguide/Query.html

